<div id="pfb" class="pf w0 h0" data-page-no="b"><div class="pc pcb w0 h0"><div class="c x1 y1 w2 h2"><div class="t m0 x2 h3 y2 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Meadowbrook Policy 1A</div></div><div class="t m0 x2 h8 y3c ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The condition report may be <span class="_ _2"></span>signed and endorsed by the resident <span class="_ _2"></span>within three days of the <span class="_ _2"></span>resident’s arrival at </div><div class="t m0 x2 h8 y3d ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the SRS. The endorsement should state that the resident agrees with the whole of the report <span class="_ _2"></span>or identify those </div><div class="t m0 x2 h8 y3e ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">matters with which the resident does not agree.</div><div class="t m0 x2 ha y1e9 ff2 fs3 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0">Section 5</div><div class="t m0 x2 ha y1ea ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Record keeping and incident reporting: <span class="ff4 fs0">rr. 45–47 (draft), r. 54 (draft). Some of them as below,</span></div><div class="t m0 x2 hc y1eb ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">• <span class="fs0">Medication records</span></div><div class="t m0 x2 hc y1ec ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">• <span class="fs0">Resident records</span></div><div class="t m0 x2 hc y1ed ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">• <span class="fs0">Staff records</span></div><div class="t m0 x2 hc y1ee ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">• <span class="fs0">Resident transfers</span></div><div class="t m0 x2 hc y1ef ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">• <span class="fs0">Incident records</span></div><div class="t m0 x2 hc y1f0 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">• <span class="fs0">Reportable incidents.</span></div><div class="t m0 x2 h11 y1f1 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Residents’ records: <span class="ff9 fs7"> <span class="ff4 fs0">r. 46 (draft)</span></span></div><div class="t m0 x2 h8 y1f2 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Residents’ <span class="_ _3"> </span>records <span class="_ _3"> </span>will <span class="_ _4"> </span>be <span class="_ _3"> </span>kept <span class="_ _3"> </span>in <span class="_ _3"> </spa